Description:
    Generates a single MCP tool class. Pass the tool name and any arguments
    it should accept. The tool name should be in snake_case format.

    This generates a tool class in app/tools/ that inherits from MCP::Tool
    and includes the specified arguments with proper type mapping.

Example:
    `bin/rails generate mcp_tool weather_tool longitude:string latitude:string`

    Weather tool with longitude and latitude arguments.
        Tool: app/tools/weather_tool.rb

    `bin/rails generate mcp_tool user_lookup user_id:integer email:string`

    User lookup tool with user_id and email arguments.
        Tool: app/tools/user_lookup.rb

Available field types:
    string, text, integer, float, decimal, boolean, datetime, date, time, 
    references, belongs_to, timestamp, digest, attachment, token, rich_text